         <component>
            <section ID="i4i_adverse_effects_id_7ff37726-e0d5-4fea-93c6-f8f02ee59070">
               <id root="a8cd9a29-48a1-4f0c-9a7e-ed24cf6c0434"/>
               <code codeSystem="2.16.840.1.113883.6.1" code="34084-4" displayName="ADVERSE REACTIONS SECTION"/>
               <title>ADVERSE REACTIONS:</title>
               <text>
                  <paragraph>Adverse reactions have occurred with the anti-infective components of neomycin and polymyxin B sulfates and bacitracin zinc ophthalmic ointment.  The exact incidence is not known.  Reactions occurring most often are allergic sensitization reactions including itching, swelling, and conjunctival erythema (see <content styleCode="bold">WARNINGS</content>).  More serious hypersensitivity reactions, including anaphylaxis, have been reported rarely.  Local irritation on instillation has also been reported.</paragraph>
                  <paragraph>
                     <content styleCode="italics">To report SUSPECTED ADVERSE REACTIONS, contact Fera Pharmaceuticals, LLC at (414) 434-6604, Monday-Friday 9am-5pm EST or FDA at 1-800-FDA-1088 or www.fda.gov/medwatch.</content>
                  </paragraph>
               </text>
               <effectiveTime value="20110715"/>
            </section>
         </component>
         <component>
            <section ID="i4i_dosage_admin_id_18d9567d-d077-41cd-bcea-fceaf62e0b48">
               <id root="76264f46-f9c2-4c5b-8e31-de3b085b43e7"/>
               <code codeSystem="2.16.840.1.113883.6.1" code="34068-7" displayName="DOSAGE &amp; ADMINISTRATION SECTION"/>
               <title>DOSAGE AND ADMINISTRATION:</title>
               <text>
                  <paragraph>May be applied every 3 or 4 hours for 7 to 10 days, depending on the severity of the infection.<br/>
                  </paragraph>
               </text>
               <effectiveTime value="20110715"/>
            </section>
         </component>
